#PGML

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image( "21-S-5.2-RP-01.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

A bar supported by a pin connected to a smooth collar at point [`A`], a roller at point [`B`], and a cable at point [`C`] is in equilibrium. If the bar has a non-negligible mass, find the number of unknowns in the system.

If the x-axis is the horizontal axis and the y-axis is the vertical axis, select the unknown force reaction components for each support. There may be more than one correct answer.

[@ $mcA -> print_q() @]*
[@ $mcA -> print_a() @]*


[@ $mcB -> print_q() @]*
[@ $mcB -> print_a() @]*


[@ $mcC -> print_q() @]*
[@ $mcC -> print_a() @]*


Are there any couple moments formed by the supports?

[@ $mcD -> buttons() @]*


Find the possible values of the force reactions assuming that forces are positive when directed to the right or upwards and moments are positive counterclockwise.

[@ $mcE -> print_q() @]*
[@ $mcE -> print_a() @]*


[@ $mcF -> print_q() @]*
[@ $mcF -> print_a() @]*


[@ $mcG -> print_q() @]*
[@ $mcG -> print_a() @]*


[@ $mcH -> print_q() @]*
[@ $mcH -> print_a() @]*


[@ $mcI -> print_q() @]*
[@ $mcI -> print_a() @]*


[@ $mcJ -> print_q() @]*
[@ $mcJ -> print_a() @]*


END_PGML

install_problem_grader(~~&std_problem_grader);

ANS( checkbox_cmp( $mcA->correct_ans() ) );
ANS( checkbox_cmp( $mcB->correct_ans() ) );
ANS( checkbox_cmp( $mcC->correct_ans() ) );
ANS( $mcD->cmp() );
ANS( checkbox_cmp( $mcE->correct_ans() ) );
ANS( checkbox_cmp( $mcF->correct_ans() ) );
ANS( checkbox_cmp( $mcG->correct_ans() ) );
ANS( checkbox_cmp( $mcH->correct_ans() ) );
ANS( checkbox_cmp( $mcI->correct_ans() ) );
ANS( checkbox_cmp( $mcJ->correct_ans() ) );

